  "verdict": "The file-line sprawl term carries no defensible independent signal: dropping it does not reduce pooled leave-one-repo-out AUC (\u0394=-0.009) and its coefficient's 95% CI [-0.094, 0.248] spans zero. Consistent with the 0.3.0 candidate to drop or shrink it. Analysis only: no scoring or weight change ships here; any weight change stays a 0.3.0 breaking change, and the construct gap (defects \u2260 maintainability) and external-validity gap (mature OSS \u2260 the target population) remain open."
